Description: High-performance, multiplayer code editor (Official Tarball Repackage)
 Zed is a modern open-source code editor, built from the ground up in Rust
 with a GPU-accelerated renderer, from the creators of Atom and Tree-sitter.
 .
 This package repackages the official upstream Linux tarball for Debian,
 ensuring native Wayland/X11 support and bypassing source-build compiler bugs.
 .
 Note: The CLI binary is named 'zeditor' to avoid conflicts with the
 existing Debian 'zed' package (an OCaml text editor).
